Build ubuntu-oracular sdcard for raspberrypi5:

Input files: ../kernel/out/boot.img
             ../rootfs-ubuntu-oracular/linaro-rootfs.img

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC.
sudo ./mksdcardimg.sh
Eject sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.
Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to PC again
sudo mount /dev/sda1 /mnt
sudo cp /media/$USER/rootfs/boot/initrd.img-6.11.0-1004-raspi /mnt/initramfs_2712
sudo cp /media/$USER/rootfs/boot/vmlinuz-6.11.0-1004-raspi /mnt/kernel_2712.img
sudo vi /mnt/config.txt ( add usb_max_current_enable=1 )
sync
sudo umount /mnt
sudo umount /media/$USER/rootfs
Eject sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD from PC.

Plugin sdcard/USB2-SATA-SSD to rpi5.
Login:
Username: linaro
Password: linaro
Setup wifi. Disable power saving and screen saver.
sudo dpkg-reconfigure openssh-server
uname -a
lsb_release -a
sudo ifconfig
sudo dpkg-reconfigure tzdata
sudo dpkg-reconfigure locales
date
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt dist-upgrade
sudo vi /etc/systemd/logind.conf ( change to follows:
HandlePowerKey=ignore
HandleRebootKey=ignore
HandleSuspendKey=ignore
HandleHibernateKey=ignore
HandleLidSwitch=ignore
)
sync
sudo shutdown -h now
Power off, power on
glxinfo | grep OpenGL
date
Check display mode: ( wayland or x11 )
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE
Check audio driver: ( pulseaudio or pipewire )
pactl info

sudo apt install speedtest-cli python3-pip python3-setuptools ffmpeg mpv glmark2-es2-wayland pandoc

speedtest-cli --secure

glmark2-es2-wayland

aplay -l
pavucontrol  ( select card 0 as default )

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:mozillateam/ppa
sudo apt update
sudo apt install firefox-esr
firefox -> youtube.com -> search YmDNhi07_Ho

git clone https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp.git
cd yt-dlp
make
cd ../
~/yt-dlp/yt-dlp -f 'bestvideo[ext=mp4]+bestaudio[ext=m4a]' 3qrKjywjo7Q -o swan.mp4
mpv swan.mp4

sudo rfkill list
hciconfig hci0
hcitool dev
hciconfig -a
